00:01:29.730 --> 00:01:41.530
Mike: For as long as anybody remembers, the Great Chasm has split Simcova like a wound, an impossible cleft that plunges into endless depths, from which strangeness typically emerges.

33
00:01:41.530 --> 00:01:52.310
Mike: Spires of impossible buildings, unexpected lights, storms and winds that seem to defy gravity, and unusual and unseasonable plants that the Kenku sometimes harvest.

34
00:01:52.750 --> 00:02:06.080
Mike: Although many in the region see it as the home of Zephya, the cruel west wind of Zimcovan legends, not all do. The Kenku monks of the Kameko Monastery see it as a place of safety and refuge, where they can train

35
00:02:06.420 --> 00:02:18.400
Mike: unwatched by the outside world, and safe from danger. And the mystics of the Vehovacai believe the chasm is a place of elemental balance and great power.

36
00:02:19.170 --> 00:02:25.020
Mike: The summer of 1729 in Zimkova started fine and fair, but by late August.

37
00:02:25.400 --> 00:02:31.019
Mike: Rumors of an orcish horde led by a fearsome orc calling herself the Ravenger of Winter.

38
00:02:31.020 --> 00:02:33.290
Audio shared by Mike: had started to spread across Breva.

39
00:02:34.810 --> 00:02:45.299
Mike: In early September, the news came. A great battle had been fought north of the chasm between the dwarves of Nizdihar, apparently aided by a large contingent of Stoneborne and the orcish horde.

40
00:02:45.410 --> 00:02:48.750
Mike: The Ravager was killed, and the bulk of the orcs were defeated.

41
00:02:48.750 --> 00:02:54.779
Audio shared by Mike: But scattered bands fled south to Breva like angry wasps, and the Mezai, the Woodswalkers.

42
00:02:55.360 --> 00:02:59.820
Mike: And many others were kept busy defending the people from these scattered orc hordes.

43
00:03:00.630 --> 00:03:05.000
Audio shared by Mike: So few noticed as the first signs came of the chasm changing.

44
00:03:05.150 --> 00:03:10.509
Audio shared by Mike: A summer thunderstorm, thick and warm, burst forth from the chasm in October.

45
00:03:10.650 --> 00:03:20.830
Audio shared by Mike: But this had happened before, and although it wasn't common, no one really remarked on it. A sandstorm, thick and dry, with scorching heat, came out of the chasm in November.

46
00:03:21.100 --> 00:03:32.759
Audio shared by Mike: A boulder of volcanic stone, a flame with green fire, tumbled down the river that flows out of the chasm and floated all the way to the green sea, unquenched by water.

47
00:03:33.050 --> 00:03:35.499
Audio shared by Mike: That was remarked on as mighty strange.

48
00:03:38.140 --> 00:03:41.169
Mike: In December, a rainbow appeared.

49
00:03:43.060 --> 00:03:54.320
Mike: That stretched across the sky over the chasm, and a day later, it shattered into hundreds of thousands of glass shards that drifted to the ground across the chasm and fell in.

50
00:03:55.340 --> 00:03:59.130
Mike: That was widely seen as an omen, but few could say what it meant.

51
00:03:59.980 --> 00:04:12.809
Mike: When the rainbow sign was followed by a living sheet of ice that swam out of the chasm and left behind… and swam down the teft, the main river, like a predator, leaving behind dead fish and…

52
00:04:12.810 --> 00:04:20.199
Mike: frozen banks in its wake, many in Breva began to believe Xyphia was angry, and the chasm needed to be appeased.

53
00:04:20.950 --> 00:04:31.759
Mike: And then, at the start of January, the sky above the chasm turned black, and held darkness, blotting out the sun over the chasm, like a huge dark cloud on the horizon.

54
00:04:31.880 --> 00:04:33.589
Mike: For 5 days and nights.

55
00:04:34.710 --> 00:04:36.529
